text: Rodney Procter Frelinghuysen As pronounced in "Repeal and Replace ACA". (born April 29, 1946) is an American politician. He was the U.S. Representative for , serving from 1995 to 2019. Frelinghuysen has served as Chair of the House Appropriations Committee since 2017. Frelinghuysen announced on January 29, 2018, that he would not seek re-election that year. ==References== ==Other websites== * Congressman Rodney Frelinghuysen official U.S. House site * Rodney Frelinghuysen for Congress Category:1946 births Category:Living people Category:United States representatives from New Jersey Category:Politicians from New York City Category:Republican Party (United States) politicians
